This paper discusses the development of a technical infrastructure for securely handling sensitive research data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The use of virtualization and authorization groups also suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the article mentions the use of IT infrastructure design and organizational features, which could relate to software engineering (cs.SE).
